Getting Technical

Marked-Down Apparel Stocks Break Out
The clothing companies advertising in holiday sale circulars could offer similar values on their stocks.


 







By

Michael Kahn

 Biography




 




July 5, 2017


Two of the most widely followed apparel makers saw their stocks collapse in dramatic fashion over the past year. But quietly, away from the spotlight, several peer stocks broke out to the upside last month. Others appear ready to follow soon. The big losers included sports-apparel maker Under Armour (ticker: UAA), which fell from roughly $54 per share in 2015 to its low near $17 earlier this year. The decline included several multi-percentage-point single-day drops along the way. Lululemon Athletica (LULU) also suffered...
	      




 


